ROUNDCUBE PLUS NEWS FEED PLUGIN
===============================

This plugin displays a news feed on the mail page sidebar.

REQUIREMENTS
------------
- Roundcube: 1.5, 1.6
- PHP: 7.4 or higher
- PHP cURL extension

INSTALLATION
------------
1. Copy the directories xnews_feed and xframework included in this package to the 'plugins' directory of your Roundcube
   installation.

2. Rename the file <roundcube>/plugins/xnews_feed/config.inc.php.dist to config.inc.php.

3. Edit the file <roundcube>/plugins/xnews_feed/config.inc.php and configure the plugin according to your needs.

4. Edit the file <roundcube>/config/config.inc.php, add xnews_feed to the plugins array and specify your license key.

For more information on installing Roundcube Plus plugins see:
https://roundcubeplus.com/helpdesk/knowledgebase.php?article=29

The users can change the plugin settings in the news feed section of the Settings page. They can remove the feed
from the sidebar by unchecking "Show news feed feed" in the Sidebar section of the Settings page.

COMPATIBILITY
-------------
This plugin has been created for the standard version of Roundcube as provided on the Roundcube website:
https://roundcube.net. It might not work properly with customized versions of Roundcube including the version
provided as part of the Kolab system. Please note that we cannot provide any technical support for the plugin
deployed on a non-standard version of Roundcube.

